<title>LEBANON: GOVERNMENT LIST.</title>
<headline>GOVERNMENT LIST.</headline>
<text>
<p>LEBANON GOVERNMENT LIST (961022)</p>
<p> **************************************************************</p>
<p> * 15 Oct 96 - Prime Minister Hariri and his 29-member	  *</p>
<p> *		 government resigned to make way for the	  *</p>
<p> *		 formation of a new government following recent *</p>
<p> *		 parliamentary elections.			     *</p>
<p> **************************************************************</p>
<p>				- - - - - - -</p>
<p> President.....................Elias HRAWI (Maronite Christian)</p>
<p>(Six-year term expired 24 Nov 95, but was extended for a</p>
<p>further 3 years by parliament)</p>
<p>				- - - - - - -</p>
<p>OUTGOING COALITION CABINET (Formed 25 May 95))</p>
<p> Prime Minister..................Rafik al-HARIRI (Sunni Moslem)</p>
<p>(Apptd 21 May 95)</p>
<p>(Also Finance Minister)</p>
<p>  Deputy Prime Minister.........Michel al-MURR (Greek Orthodox)</p>
<p>(Also Interior Minister)</p>
<p>				- - - - - - -</p>
<p>MINISTERS:</p>
<p> Agriculture...................Shawki FAKHOURY (Greek Orthodox)</p>
<p> Culture, Higher Education...............Michel EDDE (Maronite)</p>
<p> Defence........................Mohsen DALLOUL (Shi'ite Moslem)</p>
<p> Displaced People........................Walid JUMBLATT (Druze)</p>
<p> Economy, Trade..........................Yassin JABER (Shi'ite)</p>
<p> Education, Youth......................Robert GHANEM (Maronite)</p>
<p> Electricity, Water Resources..........Elias HOBEIKA (Maronite)</p>
<p> Emigrants..............................Ali al-KHALIL (Shi'ite)</p>
<p> Environment....................Pierre PHARAON (Greek Catholic)</p>
<p> Finance.....................................See Prime Minister</p>
<p> Foreign Affairs.........................Faris BOUEZ (Maronite)</p>
<p> Health...................................Marwan HAMADE (Druze)</p>
<p> Housing, Cooperatives.............Mahmoud Abu HAMDAN (Shi'ite)</p>
<p> Industry &amp; Oil.....................Chahe BARSOUMIAN (Armenian)</p>
<p> Information......................Farid MAKARI (Greek Orthodox)</p>
<p> Interior.........................................See Deputy PM</p>
<p> Justice...................................Bahij TABARA (Sunni)</p>
<p> Labour...........................Assad HARDAN (Greek Orthodox)</p>
<p>Municipalities &amp; Rural Affairs....Hagop DEMOURIJIAN (Armenian)</p>
<p> Posts, Communications..................Al-Fadel CHALAQ (Sunni)</p>
<p> Public Works.............................Ali HARAJLI (Shi'ite)</p>
<p> Social Affairs..................Estefan ad-DOUWAIHI (Maronite)</p>
<p>Technical &amp; Vocational Education.....Abdul-Rahim MURAD (Sunni)</p>
<p> Tourism......................Nichola FATTOUSH (Greek Catholic)</p>
<p> Transportation............................Omar MISKAWI (Sunni)</p>
<p>				- - - - - - -</p>
<p>MINISTERS OF STATE:</p>
<p> Financial Affairs........................Fouad SINIORA (Sunni)</p>
<p> Administrative Reform..................Anwar al-KHALIL (Druze)</p>
<p>							Hani SHAKAR (Shi'ite)</p>
<p>					 Kabalan Isa al-KHOURY (Maronite)</p>
<p>					     Nadim SALEM (Greek Catholic)</p>
<p>				- - - - - - -</p>
<p> Parliament Speaker.......................Nabih BERRI (Shi'ite)</p>
<p>(Re-elected for second four-year term 22 Oct 96)</p>
<p>				- - - - - - -</p>
<p> Central Bank Governor.............................Riad SALAMEH</p>
<p>				- - - - - - -</p>
<p>	 NOTE: Any comments/queries on the content of this</p>
<p>		 government list, please contact the Reuter</p>
<p>		 Editorial Reference Unit, London, on (171) 542</p>
<p>		 7968.</p>
<p>			 (End government list)</p>
